comment: It is believed that a(n) is always > 0.

maple: read transforms; M:=100000; sp:=1; a:=[sp]; s:=sp;
for n from 2 to M do sp:=digsum(s); a:=[op(a),sp]; s:=s+sp; od:
if member(n,a,'p') then b:=[op(b),p] else b:=[op(b),-1]; fi;
